      "body": "## Security Requirement\n\nAs part of our SOC2 Type II compliance efforts, we need to implement encryption at rest for all customer data stored in our systems.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Enable S3 bucket encryption with customer-managed KMS keys\n- [ ] Implement RDS encryption for all databases containing customer data\n- [ ] Enable EBS volume encryption for application servers\n- [ ] Document encryption key rotation procedures\n- [ ] Update security policies to reflect encryption requirements\n\n## Related Controls\n\n- **CC6.8**: The entity implements logical access security measures to protect against threats from sources outside its system boundaries.\n- **CC6.1**: The entity implements logical access security software, infrastructure, and architectures over protected information assets.\n\n## Timeline\n\nThis must be completed before the Q4 SOC2 audit scheduled for December 2024.\n\n## Additional Context\n\nThis addresses findings from our internal security assessment and aligns with industry best practices for data protection.",
