      "body": "## Compliance Requirement\n\nPer SOC2 CC8.1 requirements, we need comprehensive audit logging for all privileged access events within our systems.\n\n## Current State\n\n- Basic application logging exists\n- AWS CloudTrail is configured for API calls\n- No centralized audit log aggregation\n- Limited monitoring of privileged operations\n\n## Requirements\n\n### CC8.1 - Change Tracking\n- [ ] Log all administrative access attempts (successful and failed)\n- [ ] Track configuration changes to security-sensitive systems\n- [ ] Monitor privileged user activities\n- [ ] Implement log integrity protection\n- [ ] Establish log retention policies (7 years minimum)\n\n### Technical Implementation\n- [ ] Configure AWS CloudTrail for comprehensive API logging\n- [ ] Set up VPC Flow Logs for network activity\n- [ ] Implement application-level audit logging\n- [ ] Configure AWS Config for configuration change tracking\n- [ ] Set up CloudWatch for real-time monitoring and alerting\n\n### Monitoring and Alerting\n- [ ] Root account usage alerts\n- [ ] Failed authentication attempt monitoring\n- [ ] Privilege escalation detection\n- [ ] Unusual access pattern alerts\n- [ ] Log tampering detection\n\n## Evidence Collection\n\nThe following evidence must be available for auditors:\n- Audit log configurations\n- Sample audit logs showing tracked events\n- Incident response procedures\n- Log retention and protection policies\n- Monitoring and alerting configurations\n\n## Timeline\n\n- **Phase 1** (Aug 2024): CloudTrail and Config setup\n- **Phase 2** (Sep 2024): Application audit logging\n- **Phase 3** (Oct 2024): Monitoring and alerting\n- **Phase 4** (Nov 2024): Documentation and testing\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- All privileged operations are logged with sufficient detail\n- Logs are tamper-evident and securely stored\n- Real-time alerting for critical security events\n- Compliance team can generate audit reports\n- External auditors can verify log completeness and integrity",
